in London, Paris, and Berlin. Linking Britain’s declaration of war on Germany in 1914 to Ghadar’s declaration of war on Britain, Ramnath vividly recounts how 8,000 rebels were deployed from around the world to take up the battle in Hindustan. Haj to Utopia demonstrates how far-flung freedom fighters managed to articulate a radical new world order out of seemingly contradictory ideas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNationalismxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical activistsxHistoryy20th century. 0aRevolutionariesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial movementsxHistoryy20th century. 0aSocial reformersxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld politicsy1900-1918. 0aWorld politicsy1919-1932. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  a20th century europe.  a20th century india.  a20th century politics.  aasian diaspora.  abritish empire and india.  abritish history.  abritish rule.  acalifornia history.  acalifornia immigration.  aeuropean history.  agerman empire.  aglobal radicalism.  agovernment and governing.  ahistory of india.  aimperial history.  aimperialism and nationalism.  aindian colonialism.  aindian history.  aindians and california.  apolitical radicalism.  apolitics.  aradical political thought.  aradical thought.  asouth asian immigrants.  aus history.  awest coast.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026954540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095039940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950399423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950399/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY